## `test_read_partial_past_eof_returns_truncated(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-6 -->

### Purpose
A read that starts inside the file but extends past EOF returns only the bytes that exist (short read is valid, not an error).

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"hello", offset=0)
assert fs.read(fd, size=100, offset=2) == b"llo"
```

---

## `test_write_past_eof_zero_pads_gap(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-7 -->

### Purpose
Writing at an offset beyond current EOF zero-fills the intervening bytes (POSIX semantics for a non-sparse file).

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"end", offset=100)
assert fs.stat("/f").size == 103
# Bytes 0..100 are zero.
assert fs.read(fd, size=100, offset=0) == b"\x00" * 100
# Bytes 100..103 are the written data.
assert fs.read(fd, size=3, offset=100) == b"end"
```

---

## `test_truncate_to_zero_removes_all_chunks(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-8 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"x" * (CHUNK * 3), offset=0)
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 3

fs.truncate_fd(fd, 0)
assert fs.stat("/f").size == 0
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 0
assert fs.read(fd, size=100, offset=0) == b""
```

---

## `test_truncate_shrink_removes_trailing_chunks(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-9 -->

### Purpose
Shrinking truncate frees every chunk whose start offset is beyond the new size, and truncates the chunk that contains the new EOF.

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"x" * (CHUNK * 3 + 100), offset=0)      # 3 full chunks + 100 bytes in chunk 3
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 4

fs.truncate_fd(fd, CHUNK + 500)                        # keep chunk 0 (full) + 500 bytes of chunk 1
assert fs.stat("/f").size == CHUNK + 500
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 2
```

---

## `test_truncate_grow_zero_pads(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-10 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"abc", offset=0)
fs.truncate_fd(fd, 10)

assert fs.stat("/f").size == 10
assert fs.read(fd, size=10, offset=0) == b"abc" + b"\x00" * 7
```

