## `test_overwrite_middle_keeps_chunk_count(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-12 -->

### Purpose
Overwriting bytes in the middle of an existing chunk leaves `_count_chunks` unchanged — we update in place, not append.

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"x" * 1000, offset=0)
chunks_before = fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode)

fs.write(fd, b"yy", offset=100)
chunks_after = fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode)

assert chunks_before == chunks_after
data = fs.read(fd, size=1000, offset=0)
assert data[:100] == b"x" * 100
assert data[100:102] == b"yy"
assert data[102:] == b"x" * 898
```

---

## `test_exact_chunk_boundary_write(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-13 -->

### Purpose
A write of exactly CHUNK bytes starting at offset 0 fills chunk 0 precisely and produces no chunk 1.

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
fs.write(fd, b"a" * CHUNK, offset=0)
assert fs.stat("/f").size == CHUNK
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 1

# A 1-byte write at CHUNK creates chunk 1.
fs.write(fd, b"b", offset=CHUNK)
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 2
assert fs.stat("/f").size == CHUNK + 1
```

---

## `test_large_file_multi_chunk(fs_with_file)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-14 -->

### Purpose
A 10-chunk-sized write writes correctly across all ten chunks and reads back byte-identical.

### Postconditions

```python
fs, fd = fs_with_file
payload = bytes((i & 0xFF) for i in range(CHUNK * 10))
fs.write(fd, payload, offset=0)

assert fs.stat("/f").size == CHUNK * 10
assert fs._count_chunks(fs.stat("/f").inode) == 10

# Byte-identical readback.
assert fs.read(fd, size=CHUNK * 10, offset=0) == payload
```

---

## `test_content_survives_reopen(tmp_db)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-blobs-15 -->

### Purpose
Content written + committed is durable: after close + reopen, every byte reads back identically.

### Postconditions

```python
from sqlite_fs import mkfs, open_fs

mkfs(str(tmp_db))
fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
with fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fd = fs.create("/f")
    fs.write(fd, b"persisted", offset=0)
    fs.close_fd(fd)
fs.close()

fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
with fs.as_user(0, 0):
    fd = fs.open("/f", flags=0)
    assert fs.read(fd, size=9, offset=0) == b"persisted"
    fs.close_fd(fd)
fs.close()
```

